Definition: a striped mass of white and grey matter located in front of the thalamus in each cerebral hemisphere
Example: consists of the caudate nucleus and the lenticular nucleus
Synonyms: striatum, striate_body, basal_ganglion, a, striped, mass, of, white, and, grey, matter, located, in, front, the, thalamus, each, cerebral, hemisphere, consists, caudate, nucleus, lenticular
Category: noun.body
